														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1223918">
									

<p>I can fix this. I'll strain out all the clichés I can, but a few of them are necessary.</p>
<p>1: The interior has to be indestructible, otherwise someone would punch a hole in it and take a peek outside.<br />
2: If it's indestructible, you can't really test it thoroughly, so it's going to be unknown. What if I added a few more details about the material from non-invasive tests/observations?<br />
3: It also has to be some kind of portal, otherwise you could punch a hole in the exterior and take a peek <em>in</em>side.</p>
<p>The impossible dimensions thing can be taken out, you're right about that.</p>
<p>As for the Experiment log, I did think about having the mummified guy go crazy and write stuff on the walls. The problem is, he's not in there for all eternity, only until he dies of dehydration. A few days isn't enough time to start flinging faeces, if you know what I mean. The last entry was supposed to suggest shenanigans, with the internment of multiple subjects allowing for acts of violence and cannibalism, but I went for the less is more approach. Maybe it's not quite enough. I'll try to add a few more grotesque elements.</p>
<p>Tomorrow, though. It's 1am and time to sleep.</p>

