<p>Well, for starters, the foundation would probably try locking someone in with a supply of food and water- that way, if it skips them a week ahead they'll still be alive to answer questions- also, it would allow you to use the going crazy/isolation thing in the experiment logs.</p>
<p>It could probably also do without being indestructible- just make it a standard shipping container with the weird time effect, maybe highly resilient to corrosion or rust (which would give the foundation something more to study, since 'twould be more of an asset than time room)- or add something else in if that's a bit too plain. I would say voices that tell the person they'll be trapped for eternity, but that may be in violation of a cliche as well.</p>

