<p>Blegh, downvoted for being really, really, really mediocre. It is well written and the tone is solid, but the idea itself just does nothing for me. It's a box that makes time flow weird&#8230;.so? This lacks any kind of hook to grab and hold my attention.</p>
<p>Also, I know some people will disagree strongly with me, but I don't think you need to cover your ass from inquiries at every turn. The interior doesn't need to be indestructible; the Foundation probably wouldn't risk destroying the object by damaging the interior unless we have reason to believe there was something genuinely valuable to be gained in doing so. Also, why wouldn't an hourglass work (I mean both in universe and out). It is completely illogical for it to not work since really ANYTHING can be used to track time if you know how. I get that you added it, though, as a way to prevent people reading this from poking holes in it. What I don't get it what good it does the article? So what if we can record exactly what the time dilation effects are? What is the harm in that?</p>

